    <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>About Us</strong></p>
<p>Contour is looking for motivated and highly talented individuals to help grow the company and achieve its hugely ambitious goal. Contour prides itself on having an excellent internal culture, where we strive hard to create the best possible working environment: a healthy mix of change, fast pace, supportive atmosphere, ecosystem collaboration and of course, fun.</p>
<p>Contour hires team members of excellent calibre in every role. While a lot will be asked of you, you will benefit greatly from working in open, collaborative team, with colleagues who excel. Working at Contour is fast-paced and team-oriented with an emphasis in delivering the highest quality work in every field to ensure our own and our member's success as we reshape the industry.</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>Context of the role:</strong></p>
<p>Reporting to the Chief Product Officer, the Head of Engineering is responsible setting the technical strategy and managing the teams responsible for building our decentralised network. You will work closely with the Product team to define future requirements, with the engineering leads for their implementation and the operations team to ensure a successful rollout and implementation. You will be hands-on where required to demonstrate your deep technical understanding and commitment to quality. You will also be expected to maintain knowledge of the latest application technology trends (Web 3, Defi) and collaborate with our partners and customers on industry-transforming solutions.</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul><li>Maintain an active understanding of the latest technology trends and their potential use within to Contour, reporting regularly to senior management</li><li>Formulate and deliver the technical strategy for the company aligned to the business objectives</li><li>Ownership of all delivery against agreed scope and plans.</li><li>Collaborate closely with the People team for day to day management of the engineering team and 3rd party vendors.</li><li>Drive continuous improvement within the team - increasing delivery efficiency, improving quality and team happiness.</li><li>Represent engineering strategy and interests when partnering with the Product Team to plan the product roadmap</li><li>Work with Contour’s partners and customers to design multi-company/system architectures.</li></ul>
<p><br /></p><p><h2>Requirements:</h2></p><p><strong>Key Requirements</strong></p>
<ul><li>5+ years of relevant experience in leading high performing engineering teams using the latest technology stacks.</li><li>7-10 years experience as a senior software engineer in at least 1 programming language (Java, JavaScript, Python, Go, etc), with hands-on experience in many others.</li><li>Solid understanding of Web 3.0 and blockchain/DLT architectures.</li><li>Track record of inspiring, leading and growing high performing teams across geographies</li><li>Be hands-on where required to resolve conflicts with the team or to support production incidents</li><li>Hands on experience with modern development tooling (IDE’s, build and deployment pipelines, git, etc)</li><li>Hands on experience with public cloud providers like AWS, Azure, GCP</li><li>Strong understanding on how web application work and the fundamentals behind them (i.e. HTTP, DNS, Web Servers, etc)</li><li>Proven experience in analysing and decision making for both technical and non-technical decisions</li><li>Confident and comfortable presenting and facilitating meetings for large audiences</li><li>Strong analytical skills to question architecture and product decisions</li><li>Able to demonstrate a strong understanding of modern SDLC methodologies</li><li>Effective communication with cross functional team members, business stakeholders and external parties</li><li>Nice to have<ul><li>Publishing of Technica papers / participation in technology forms, seminars</li><li>Hands-on experience with blockchain technologies</li><li>Financial / Trade finance domain knowledge</li></ul></li></ul>]]></description>
