    <description><![CDATA[<p>Wyre is on a mission to bring crypto to the masses.<br></p><p>To accomplish this mission, we’ve built a simple set of tools that allow developers to materialize their projects. Our fiat-to-crypto Checkout gateway is now being used by hundreds of applications (like MetaMask, Opera, Brave, and BRD) to offer the easiest way to convert payments into crypto. Our flexible White-Label Payment APIs (Transfers API, Custody API, and Users API), enable developers to build e-wallets, merchant processing services, and money transfer platforms from the ground up.</p><p>We focus on compliance, licensing, liquidity, and payment processing services so our partners can do what they do best, creating amazing tools on the blockchain.</p><p>We are looking for a highly motivated, entrepreneurial and experienced legal support lead to join our legal team as Legal Program Manager. This position will report to our General Counsel. The Legal Program Manager will focus his or her practice on providing a broad range of commercial, litigation and regulatory support for the legal department, including contract management, managing law enforcement requests, and supporting audit and the finance teams to provide responsive documentation. Although the role is focused on managing commercial, litigation and regulatory program support, this person is also expected to support the needs of the business generally, and accordingly, can expect to be involved in the variety of novel issues arising in crypto. This role requires high EQ, the ability to navigate complex organizational dynamics and a healthy dose of humor.</p> <p>What You’ll Be Doing</p><ul> <li>Support the Legal department and the Sales and Business Development teams in contract management, including organizing information/data on potential commercial partners and preparing NDA, servicing and referral agreements using templates prepared by commercial counsel.</li> <li>Support a contract and document management system to track, store and recall commercial agreements, RFIs and related materials used to grow the organization.  </li> <li>Act as primary legal support for incoming requests for criminal investigations, including subpoenas, court orders, and law enforcement agency requests, and work cross-departmentally to collect data and information necessary to reply.</li> <li>Act of legal support to the Compliance and FInance teams in responding to certain state regulatory requests, for example, managing the escheatment program.</li> <li>Create, maintain and update index of active litigation, law enforcement and compliance matters.</li> <li>General legal administrative duties, compiling signatures and maintaining filing systems and digital databases/e-signature systems.</li> </ul> <p><br></p><p><br></p><ul> <li>Bachelor’s degree and ABA paralegal certificate preferred with current MCLE with 5+ years of experience as a contract manager or paralegal in a transactional legal environment.</li> <li>Relevant experience with an understanding of licensing, compliance and litigation.</li> <li>Technologically savvy, preferably has used or implemented a contract management system</li> <li>Driven, self-motivated, responsible and reliable with high attention to detail</li> <li>Strong organizational, project/process management, written and verbal communication skills as well as the ability to develop strong working relationships within an organization, including senior management.</li> <li>Prior experience in a fast-paced law firm or corporate environment.</li> <li>Passion and knowledge for the crypto industry!</li> </ul><ul> <li>An opportunity to build the future and freedom to work wherever you want</li> <li>Health, dental, and vision benefits for you and your family</li> <li>Life insurance and disability benefits</li> <li>Equity options for all full-time employees</li> <li>401(k) plan with corporate matching</li> <li>Unlimited paid time off to relax and recharge</li> <li>Enjoy a highly fulfilling, mission-driven culture</li> <li>You are an owner! We offer stock options to each of our employee</li> <li>Fair pay, no matter where you live along with a competitive benefits package</li> </ul><p><figure><iframe style="width: 500px; height: 281px;" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/XF10lmj4V1M" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></figure></p>]]></description>
