    <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>Are you a passionate and enthusiastic Business Development executive with an entrepreneurial mindset? Have you built a successful SaaS sales team for an early stage startup? Do this again with the support of a Series C company!</strong></p> <p><strong>The impact you will have:</strong></p><p>Elliptic is looking for a Head of Business Development to join our small, autonomous market intelligence team (MINT) which believes in a customer-centric approach to product development. We believe that the fastest route to great products is to involve our customers in every stage of the process, listen to them with empathy, enabling us to fail quickly and cheaply so that we can learn and succeed rapidly.</p> <p>We want someone who is ambitious, passionate and customer-focused. This is a unique opportunity to champion uncovering and developing new customer relationships globally for a brand new product in what will feel like a startup inside a scaleup. It is an exciting opportunity to be one of the first commercial hires on the ground helping develop Elliptic’s new product offering in the market intel space and build out a team around this. </p> <p>The role is cross-functional and global. It will be part of a small, dedicated Market Intelligence team (MINT) with a lot of independence to move quickly and be experimental, and some collaboration with the wider Elliptic team. As a Head of business development you will be proactively identifying prospective customers and generating qualified pipeline. You will also educate prospective customers about Elliptic’s new value propositions. </p> <p>We believe that the most innovative solutions arise from empowered and diverse cross functional teams who are focused on creative problem solving together.</p><p><strong>What you will do:</strong></p><ul> <li>Join a dedicated cross-functional team tasked with bringing a new product to market and be responsible for the commercial approach end-to-end, working with business leaders, data science, product, and engineers. You will be a business development team of 1 to start with.</li> <li>Build relationships with key stakeholders at prospects and customers of Elliptic’s other products outside of MINT</li> <li>Understand prospects’ requirements and identify strong collaborators for product co-creation</li> </ul><ul> <li>Proactively search for leads and prospect customers via phone, emails, social media and other outbound sales tactics </li> <li>Identify channel partnership opportunities that will enhance path to monetization and ROI </li> <li>Presenting Elliptic’s MINT value propositions including demo of our solution</li> <li>Identify &amp; qualify sales opportunities and manage the pipeline</li> <li>Work closely with marketing, product marketing, and other team members to create &amp; deliver outbound campaigns</li> <li>Identify and participate in relevant industry events to build relationships &amp; promote Elliptic</li> <li>Build out the wider MINT sales team and commercial engine </li> </ul><p><strong>Company description</strong></p> <p>At Elliptic, we believe cryptocurrency will play a huge role in the future of value transfer, and we care deeply about helping to build this future. In order for cryptocurrency to flourish, it’s important to prevent criminal abuse of the technology. Elliptic is the global leader in detecting, preventing, and pursuing criminal activity in cryptocurrencies. Our clients include the world’s leading cryptocurrency exchanges, financial institutions and government agencies.</p> <p>Our unique platform gives us an unparalleled understanding of cryptocurrency capital flows, using a combination of network science and machine learning to aggregate and interpret vast quantities of transaction data. We provide anti-money laundering (AML) compliance software and investigative services to the leading participants in the cryptocurrency ecosystem. Customers rely on us to analyse more than $150bn of their transactions every month, and include cryptocurrency businesses, major financial institutions, and federal government agencies.</p> <p>The MINT team is a new business unit that’s led by one of our co-founders and has been set up to further leverage Elliptic’s data set for crypto trading use cases. It functions as a startup inside a scaleup and is a unique opportunity to be involved in a high growth business from the ground up - all the thrill of building something new, but without the risk of joining a startup that runs out of funding. </p> <p>The company has offices in London, San Francisco, New York City, Singapore and Tokyo. We are a Series C company, backed by Evolution Equity Partners, SoftBank, SBI Group, Albion VC, Octopus Ventures, SignalFire, Paladin Capital, Santander InnoVentures, and Digital Currency Group.</p><p><strong>You’ll be a good fit here if you:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Possess enthusiasm &amp; experience in lead generation and relationship development using multiple mediums </li> <li>Have the intellectual heft to handle a technical domain with demanding customers and act as a thought partner to Product / Tech leadership</li> <li>Bring educational zeal; you engage and empower others with your content and enthusiasm</li> <li>Are a team player and cross-functional collaborator: bridging teams, functions and geographies</li> <li>Have demonstrated success in qualifying leads and building a strong pipeline, especially for new products  </li> <li>Can manage opportunities through the sales cycle</li> <li>Have the ability to easily understand and pitch new products and technology, focusing on value statements</li> <li>Have worked in financial services, alt data space selling to traders</li> <li>Have excellent written and spoken communication skills as well as presentation skills, including ability to communicate complex concepts simply to customers</li> <li>Have an entrepreneurial mindset &amp; excited about being a member of a dynamic &amp; growing team</li> <li>Have ambition. Things move quickly at Elliptic and we’re growing fast</li> <li>Have a passion for or serious desire to learn about crypto</li> <li>Have organisation: you bring order and structure to chaos</li> <li>Have experience of working with senior stakeholders </li> </ul><p><strong>You need:</strong></p><ul> <li>High intellectual curiosity, and ability to deeply understand customer requirements and communicate them back to the internal team</li> <li>Strong outbound prospecting skills, and good knowledge of outbound campaign management </li> <li>Proven track record of generating strong pipeline &amp; new logo acquisition, preferably in a SaaS or fintech environment</li> <li>Strong solution sales skills with knowledge of producing commercial proposals including RFP management</li> <li>Knowledge of the financial markets or digital assets industry</li> <li>Willing to travel, if required</li> </ul><ul> <li>Competitive salary and commission structure</li> <li>Share options</li> <li>Private health insurance</li> <li>Strong focus on personal development with $1,000 per annum personal training budget &amp; LinkedIn Learning subscription</li> <li>Collaborative, flexible and friendly environment</li> <li>Social events which include monthly team lunch on us, quarterly full-day events and an annual company 3 day event</li> </ul><p>And you get to be part of a business with a purpose, working with a passionate team of mission-driven people who’ll stretch and challenge you</p><p>Elliptic is not a traditional financial services firm. We pride ourselves on having a laid-back and friendly ethos, while still expecting great things from our team. Fascinating work is the norm - working at Elliptic is never boring!<br></p> <p>No recruitment agencies please!</p>We know Diversity and Inclusion is much deeper than just hiring, but it’s important for us to mention it here.  We welcome and embrace individuals of all backgrounds and identities at Elliptic, and this is an ongoing priority for us.  We know incredible people don’t all think in the same way.  We want to be challenged every day.  We believe our diverse team of individuals underpins this by bringing creative thinking and innovation to Elliptic every day.  We are committed to creating a diverse, inclusive and equitable workplace, so we welcome applications from everyone, even if you may not think you fit all of the requirements of our roles.  We foster an environment of psychological safety, where everyone feels comfortable to bring their whole self to work<p><figure><iframe style="width: 500px; height: 281px;" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/ebOLNjlYiNg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></figure></p>]]></description>
